ce:section.ce:para:
Under the chosen experimental conditions, the influence of the concentration of CySH on the absorption spectra was studied. As displayed in Fig. 5
                        a, the absorbance at 652 nm decreases with the increase of CySH concentration from 0.5–40 μM and the color of the corresponding solution changes from blue to transparent colorless (Fig. 5a Inset). The decrease of absorbance (ΔA) is linear to CySH concentration in the range of 0.5–20 μM (Fig. 5b) with a linear equation ΔA = 0.0362C (μM) + 0.0374 and R2 = 0.9933. The limit of detection (LOD) at an S/N ratio of 3 for CySH is 0.4 μM, indicating high sensitivity for CySH detection. The relative standard deviation (RSD) for eight repeated measurements is 2.3 % for 8.0 μM CySH, suggesting a good repeatability of this method. We compared the linear range and detection limit of this method with those from literatures (Table 1
                        ). It is evident that the proposed method is superior to most of the approaches for CySH detection in sensitivity or linear range. Replacing CySH with GSH and HcySH, similar results could be obtained (Figs. S8 and S9). The LODs for GSH and HcySH are 0.6 and 0.9 μM, respectively.
